>
>>Easiest thing you can do for a start, is to unscrew your door handles and
>keep them out of sight, either under your dash on the package shelf, or if
>you have a walk-thru (as I do), stick 'em on the floor between the seats.
>I've been doing that for 29 years, and it thwarted two break-ins in the
>70's (side windows pushed back, no entry), and who knows how many others.
